{
  "texts": [
    "First and foremost, the outcome has to be an individual decision.",
    "According to Bygrave, the term \"decision\" should be broadly interpreted and include a \"particular attitude or stance is taken towards a person\" with binding effects.",
    "28 National Data Protection Authorities (DPAs) and courts have considered cases where an automated system was used by public administrations 29 or private companies, especially in the gig economy sector.",
    "30 Under Article 22 GDPR, whether the decisionmaker is public or private is irrelevant.",
    "Instead, what is crucial is whether the decision has legal or similarly significant effects on the individual."
  ]
}